  "prompt": "How many degrees of crankshaft rotation does it take to complete one complete engine cycle in a 4 stroke engine?",
  "response": "In a 4-stroke engine, it takes **720 degrees** of crankshaft rotation to complete one complete engine cycle. This is because a 4-stroke cycle consists of four strokes: intake, compression, power, and exhaust, which requires two complete revolutions of the crankshaft (360 degrees per revolution). Thus, \\(360 \\, \\text{degrees} \\times 2 = 720 \\, \\text{degrees}\\).",
